Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows hypoglycemia with low HbA1c, elevated creatinine, and proteinuria, suggesting possible chronic kidney disease with impaired glucose metabolism. Urine findings (glucosuria, ketonuria, proteinuria, low specific gravity, brown color, ammoniacal odor) may indicate renal tubular dysfunction or possible dehydration. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal function, glycemic status, and assessment for underlying causes of hypoglycemia.
